data.enText: mold
a container that you pour a soft liquid or substance into, which then becomes solid in the same shape as the container, for example when it is cooled or cooked

data.chText: 用黏土模具来浇铸青铜塑像。
data.enText: A clay mould is used for casting bronze statues.

data.chText: 将巧克力倒入心形模子。
data.enText: Pour the chocolate into a heart-shaped mould.
They broke the mould when they made you (= there is nobody like you) .
a particular style showing the characteristics, attitudes or behaviour that are typical of sb/sth
a hero in the ‘Superman’ mould

data.chText: 他和他的前任性格不一样。
data.enText: He is cast in a different mould from his predecessor.

data.chText: 她不像一个传统的学者。
data.enText: She doesn't fit (into) the traditional mould of an academic.
a fine soft green, grey or black substance like fur that grows on old food or on objects that are left in warm wet air
There's mould on the cheese.
moulds and fungi
mould growth
break the mould (of sth)
to change what people expect from a situation, especially by acting in a dramatic and original way
to shape a soft substance into a particular form or object by pressing it or by putting it into a mould

data.chText: 首先，将陶土做成需要的形状。
data.enText: First, mould the clay into the desired shape.

data.chText: 这座人像是用黏土塑造的。
data.enText: The figure had been moulded in clay.
to strongly influence the way sb's character, opinions, etc. develop

data.chText: 这次经历影响了她的一生。
data.enText: The experience had moulded and coloured her whole life.

data.chText: 他将他们塑造成一支非凡的队伍。
data.enText: He moulded them into a superb team.
to fit or make sth fit tightly around the shape of sth
The fabric moulds to the body.

ex.chText: 他知道如何锻造一把剑。
ex.enText: He knew how to forge a sword.

ex.chText: 锻造刀刃需要高超的技能。
ex.enText: To forge a blade takes great skill.

synonyms.bx: 指把金属加热后用锤子等进行加工。

ex.chText: 使者带来了一座青铜铸像。
ex.enText: The envoy brought a statue cast in bronze.

synonyms.bx: 指将金属、塑料等加热熔化后倒入模型里，冷却后凝固成器物。

ex.chText: 这个人像是用黏土塑造的吗？
ex.enText: Is this figure moulded in clay?

ex.chText: 孩子把蜡捏成了一根蜡烛。
ex.enText: The child moulded the wax into a candle.

synonyms.bx: 指通过按压、滚动柔软物质或将其放入模具中使之成形。

data.enText: break the mould (of sth)
to change what people expect from a situation, especially by acting in a dramatic and original way

tr: container into which liquid is poured to create a given shape when it hardens
a distinctive nature, character, or type
example: a leader in the mold of her predecessors

tr: a dish or dessert that is formed in or on a mold
example: a gelatin dessert made in a mold

tr: a fungus that produces a superficial growth on various kinds of damp or decaying organic matter
the distinctive form in which a thing is made
example: pottery of this cast was found throughout the region

tr: loose soil rich in organic matter
make something, usually for a specific function
example: She molded the rice balls carefully
Work the metal into a sword

tr: form by pouring (e.g., wax or hot metal) into a cast or mold

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 mold

value.def: A mould is a hollow container that you pour liquid into. When the liquid becomes solid, it takes the same shape as the mould.

example.ex: Spoon the mixture carefully into the mould...
example.tran: 用勺小心地把混合物舀起，倒入模具内。

example.ex: The moulds for the foundry are made in the tool-room area.
example.tran: 铸造车间的模具是在工具间生产的。

value.def: If a person fits into or is cast in a mould of a particular kind, they have the characteristics, attitudes, behaviour, or lifestyle that are typical of that type of person.

example.ex: At first sight, Joe Pesci is not exactly cast in the leading man mould...
example.tran: 第一眼看上去，乔·佩希并不是当领袖的料。

example.ex: He was from the same mould as the men she had gazed at worshipfully when a child: rich, handsome, of impeccable social standing.
example.tran: 他富有、英俊，有无可挑剔的社会地位，是她孩提时就仰慕的那种男人。

defx.def: If you say that someone breaks the mould, you mean that they do completely different things from what has been done before or from what is usually done.

example.ex: Memorial services have become tedious and expected. I would like to help break the mould...
example.tran: 纪念仪式已变得令人生厌且毫无新意，我想为打破这种既有模式做点什么。

example.ex: When they first started, they said they were going to break the mould of British politics.
example.tran: 刚开始时他们说他们将打破英国政治的原有格局。

value.tran: (性格、态度、行为或生活方式的)模式，类型

value.def: If you mould a soft substance such as plastic or clay, you make it into a particular shape or into an object.

example.ex: Using 2 spoons, mould the cheese mixture into small balls or ovals...
example.tran: 用两把小匙将奶酪混合物塑成圆球或椭圆球形状。

example.ex: Before we left the camp, my twin brother and I moulded a chair out of mud.
example.tran: 离开营地前，我和孪生弟弟用泥巴做了一把椅子。

value.def: To mould someone or something means to change or influence them over a period of time so that they develop in a particular way.

example.ex: She was only 17 at the time and the experience moulded her personality...
example.tran: 那时她只有17岁，那次经历影响了她的性格。

example.ex: Here we outline some of the sometimes conflicting forces moulding the debate...
example.tran: 在此我们概述一些有时影响争论的相互对立的力量。

example.ex: Too often we try to mold our children into something they do not wish to be.
example.tran: 我们常常试图把孩子塑造成他们自己不想成为的样子。

value.def: When something moulds to an object or when you mould it there, it fits round the object tightly so that the shape of the object can still be seen.

example.ex: You need a malleable pillow that will mould to the curves of your neck...
example.tran: 你需要一个柔韧性好、能与你的颈椎弯曲弧度相吻合的枕头。

example.ex: She stood there, the wind moulding the dress around her.
example.tran: 她站在那儿，风把套裙吹得紧紧裹在身上。

value.def: Mould is a soft grey, green, or blue substance that sometimes forms in spots on old food or on damp walls or clothes.
